Name: Drew Rosenberg
AboutMe:
I started iOS development in early 2012 and participated in the summer of 2012 Coding Together experiment on Piazza. iOS development has become a big hobby of mine ever since! I have one app on the app store, which is an app that teachers can use to help streamline their running records for reader's workshop conferences. It was my wife's idea (she is 4th grade teacher) and was my final project for Coding Together.

By day, I am an R&D manager at Itron, Inc. where we develop tools to help utilities deliver gas, water, and electricity to people all over the world as efficiently and affordably as possible.
